**** types *****

var a = true; -> implicitly set to type boolean of value true.
var a:boolean=true; -> explicitly set to type boolean and set value to true.
var x:number;  --> explicitly set to type number. no value defined yet.
var b: any; --> this can be any type. you can assign it to a number, then a string, then whatever. 
var d: boolean|number|string;  --> d can be either a boolean, a number or a string.


***** functions *******

------> implictly set return type as a string
function greet(){
  return "good morning";
}

-----> explicitly set return type as a string
function greet():string {
  return "good morning";
}

function add2(a:number,b:number) --> expliclity pass two number and if not , throw an error

function add2:number(a:number,b:number)-->explictly returna  number, and pass tow numbers.

function add5(a=1:number,b=2:number):number  --> set defaults in case they are not passed.




